item.title: [+838] Vitamin D Crucial To Activating Immune Defenses
item.description: Scientists at the University of Copenhagen have discovered that Vitamin D is crucial to activating our immune defenses and that without sufficient intake of the vitamin, the killer cells of the immune system - T cells - will not be able to react to and fight off serious infections in the body.

item.title: [+708] LHC fault forces 2011 shutdown
item.description: The Large Hadron Collider must be shut down for a year starting in late 2011 to address design flaws, the BBC has learned.

item.title: [+664] Kucinich willing to be the vote that kills health reform
item.description: Facing razor-thin margins in the House, Democratic leaders are hoping to convert the sole liberal who opposes their health care bill, but it seems they have their work cut out because he isn't budging.

item.title: [+572] Lifelock Dinged $12 Million for Deceptive Business Practices
item.description: The CEO of Lifelock, Todd Davis, became famous for advertising his Social Security number on television ads and banners painted on trucks promising his $10 monthly service would protect consumers from identity theft.

item.title: [+533] Wal-Mart Sells Black Barbie for ½ the Price of White Barbie
item.description: The store was forced into the admission after a Louisiana-based shopper posted a photo of the diverse dolls—and their respective pricetags—side by side in a Wal-Mart.

item.title: [+518] 7 Muslims arrested in Ireland over plot to kill cartoonist
item.description: Seven Muslims were arrested in Ireland today over an alleged plot to assassinate a Swedish cartoonist who depicted the Prophet Mohammed with the body of a dog.

item.description: They've been plugging away for awhile now on ways to get directions for cyclists that avoids hills, excessive traffic, and points you in the best directions for pedaling to your destination. Now it's live!

item.title: [+507] Gay Porn Actor Dies on Camera After Being Tased By Police
item.description: Police arrested Andrew Grande (porn name Dustin Michaels) with a bag of weed in his possession, which he apparently tried to swallow. When he resisted arrest, they tased him, and he choked on the bag. A reality cameraman filmed it.

item.title: [+495] Woman tries to shut down Large Hadron Collider
item.description: A German woman has failed in a bid to force her country's government to halt experiments at the world's largest atom smasher which she feared would lead to the Earth's destruction.

item.title: [+490] Sony Signs All 6 Major Studios for HD Movies on PlayStation
item.description: Well, it looks like Sony has a little treat for PS3 users now that they're able to turn their consoles back on -- it's just announced that it has signed up all six major studios to deliver HD movies on the PlayStation Network (the first company to do so, as Sony is happy to point out). That includes 20th Century Fox, Walt Disney Pictures... MORE!
